==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Boa constrictor
<hw>Bo"a con*strict"or</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[NL. See <er>Boa</er>,
and <er>Constrictor</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large and
powerful serpent of tropical America, sometimes twenty or thirty feet
long. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It has a succession of spots, alternately black and
yellow, extending along the back. It kills its prey by constriction. The
name is also loosely applied to other large serpents which crush their
prey, particularly to those of the genus <gen>Python</gen>, found in
Asia and Africa.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boanerges</ent>⟦br⟧
